item.title: Ukraine Counterattack Faces Flooded Front Line
item.description: Flooding Hampers Ukrainian Counterattack in the South Ukrainian forces are planning a counterattack in the south of the country, but their efforts are being hampered by flooding. Heavy rains have caused rivers to overflow, creating a quagmire that is making it difficult for Ukrainian troops to move.
